  "articleSummary": "The article argues that the native Fetch API is now capable enough to replace Axios for most HTTP tasks, despite some ergonomic differences like automatic JSON parsing. It provides code recipes for common use cases (JSON, file uploads, timeouts, progress, cancellation) and includes a feature comparison table showing Fetch matches Axios on interceptors, cancellation, progress, and streaming. The tone is a tutorial-style advocacy piece, not a rant, aimed at web developers considering third-party HTTP libraries. The author frames the piece as \"advocacy for the `fetch` API\" and uses a \"You may not need X\" framing to encourage using built-in browser APIs.",
